/* There are several cases where the heading text is a long
   continuous string. These need to break wrap on mobile.

   The same is true for single line code examples however 
   altering the call <code> does not always work on a mobile device
   (simulator is ok) if there is more than one code line. These
   must be fixed inline. <code style="overflow-wrap: break-word;"></code>
*/
h1, h2, h3, h4, h5{
  overflow-wrap: break-word;
}

/* H5 is used in the OIS specs as a numberic heading. It is hard to 
   read the flow with so many levels. Indenting level H5 helps. It remains
   to be seen if this impacts other uses of H5 however which at this time
  (2022-02-17) do not exist.
*/
h5{
  margin-left:35px;
}

.h5-indent{
  margin-left:35px;
}


